Warped brake rotors can cause vibrations, noise, and reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. It can also lead to oil and coolant mixing, resulting in engine damage and costly repairs.
Engine oil leaks can cause a fire hazard, leading to potential accidents and injuries. They can also lead to engine damage and costly repairs.
The installation of wrong gas plugs can cause engine stalling, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. It can also lead to other engine problems and costly repairs.
The incorrect installation of spark plugs can cause the vehicle to stall intermittently, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
